## **Appendix A: Useful Code Snippets**

### **SignalBus.gd (Autoload Singleton)**

This script should be set up as an Autoload named SignalBus. It acts as a central event bus, allowing nodes to communicate without holding direct references to each other. This is a best-practice solution to avoid the "Direct Reference Obsession" anti-pattern.

\# SignalBus.gd
\# This script must be added to Project \> Project Settings \> Autoload
extends Node

\# \--- Player Signals \---
\# Emitted when the player's health changes.
signal health\_changed(current\_health: int, max\_health: int)

\# Emitted when the player's health reaches zero.
signal player\_died

\# \--- Stats & UI Signals \---
\# Emitted when the score is updated.
signal score\_updated(new\_score: int)

\# Emitted when a new item is collected (for UI, sound, etc.)
signal item\_collected(item\_resource)

\# \--- Game State Signals \---
\# Emitted by the pause menu. Listened to by enemies, players, etc.
signal game\_paused
signal game\_resumed
signal scene\_transition\_requested(scene\_path: String)

\# \--- Example Usage \---

\# In Player.gd:
\# func take\_damage(amount):
\#     health \-= amount
\#     SignalBus.health\_changed.emit(health, max\_health)
\#     if health \<= 0:
\#         SignalBus.player\_died.emit()

\# In HUD.gd:
\# func \_ready():
\#     SignalBus.health\_changed.connect(\_on\_player\_health\_changed)
\#     SignalBus.score\_updated.connect(\_on\_score\_updated)
\#
\# func \_on\_player\_health\_changed(current\_health, max\_health):
\#     health\_bar.value \= float(current\_health) / max\_health
\#
\# func \_on\_score\_updated(new\_score):
\#     score\_label.text \= str(new\_score)

### **Basic StateMachine (Component-Based)**

This pattern uses a main StateMachine node and child State nodes.

**StateMachine.gd** (Attach to a parent Node)

\# StateMachine.gd
extends Node
class\_name StateMachine

\# The state to start in. Set this in the Inspector.
@export var initial\_state: NodePath
var current\_state: State

func \_ready():
	\# Ensure all child nodes are ready first
	await get\_tree().physics\_frame

	\# Get the initial state node
	current\_state \= get\_node(initial\_state)

	\# Initialize all states
	for child in get\_children():
		if child is State:
			child.state\_machine \= self

	\# Enter the first state
	current\_state.enter()

func \_physics\_process(delta):
	current\_state.run\_physics(delta)

func \_process(delta):
	current\_state.run\_process(delta)

\# Public function to transition to a new state
func transition\_to(new\_state\_path: NodePath):
	if not has\_node(new\_state\_path):
		return

	var new\_state \= get\_node(new\_state\_path)
	if new\_state \== current\_state or not new\_state is State:
		return

	current\_state.exit()
	current\_state \= new\_state
	current\_state.enter()

**State.gd** (Base class for all states)

\# State.gd
extends Node
class\_name State

var state\_machine: StateMachine

\# Called when entering this state
func enter():
	pass

\# Called when exiting this state
func exit():
	pass

\# Called every physics frame
func run\_physics(delta):
	pass

\# Called every visual frame
func run\_process(delta):
	pass

